%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Scientists%20found%20a%20groundbreaking%20new%20reason%20to%20plant%20more%20trees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Researchers%20measure%20methane%20in%20trees%20in%20Peru.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a24d8c5a8a7bf0491966fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22562%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20measure%20methane%20in%20trees%20in%20Peru.%3Cp%3EVincent%20Gauci%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETree%20bark%20absorbs%20significant%20methane%2C%20a%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMethane%20has%2080%20times%20the%20warming%20power%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20over%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETrees'%20methane%20absorption%20could%20be%20twice%20that%20of%20Arctic%20permafrost%20emissions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETrees%20are%20a%20more%20powerful%20climate%20solution%20than%20previously%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrobes%20living%20in%20tree%20bark%20are%20absorbing%20methane%2C%20a%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas%2C%20from%20the%20atmosphere%20on%20a%20massive%20scale%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D0f9cb2b791330408d51c02001bc32140a12dd4aecfbdbc6e0e63af59838ff557%26postID%3D66a24d48c79d31931d8590cd%26postSlug%3Da-groundbreaking-new-reason-to-plant-more-trees-2024-7%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-024-07592-w%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%20Trees%20are%20sucking%20up%20just%20as%20much%2C%20if%20not%20more%2C%20methane%20than%20soil%20does%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20other%20known%20natural%20sink%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20undervaluing%20trees%20for%20their%20climate%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20Vincent%20Gauci%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Birmingham%20and%20the%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20new%20nature-based%20climate%20solution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20natural%20and%20human-made%20methane%20emissions%20from%20wetlands%2C%20cows%2C%20landfills%2C%20and%20burning%20fossil%20fuels%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%20The%20gas%20has%2080%20times%20the%20warming%20power%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20over%20two%20decades%2C%20which%20is%20why%20climate%20scientists%20say%20one%20of%20the%20fastest%20ways%20to%20slow%20global%20warming%20is%20cutting%20methane%20emissions%20and%20harnessing%20natural%20ways%20to%20remove%20it%20from%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20trees'%20ability%20to%20breathe%20in%20carbon%20dioxide%20and%20pump%20oxygen%20back%20out%20is%20well%20understood%2C%20their%20relationship%20to%20methane%20is%20more%20complex.%20Gauci%20said%20he%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20findings%2C%20which%20were%20pieced%20together%20over%20a%20decade%20by%20a%20team%20of%20international%20researchers%20measuring%20methane%20from%20trees%20in%20countries%20including%20Brazil%2C%20Peru%2C%20Panama%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20Sweden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F29211724%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202017%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20found%20that%20trees%20in%20Amazon%20floodplains%20emitted%20more%20methane%20than%20they%20absorbed.%20However%2C%20as%20researchers%20expanded%20their%20data%20collection%20to%20tropical%2C%20temperate%2C%20and%20boreal%20forests%20that%20are%20above%20floodplains%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%20upland%20%E2%80%94%20an%20opposite%20trend%20emerged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20researchers%20positions%20a%20gas%20exchange%20chambers%20on%20a%20tree%20to%20measure%20methane.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a24f2e5a8a7bf04919674b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20used%20gas%20exchange%20chambers%20to%20measure%20methane%20in%20trees.%3Cp%3EVincent%20Gauci%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20thought%20that%20if%20all%20this%20methane%20was%20being%20emitted%20from%20wetlands%2C%20maybe%20upland%20forests%20were%20contributing%20small%20amounts%20of%20emissions%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Gauci%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20found%20is%20that%20at%20the%20bottom-most%20meter%20of%20the%20tree%2C%20they%20do%20give%20off%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20methane.%20But%20the%20situation%20switches%20when%20you%20go%20up%20the%20trunk.%20We%20measured%202%2C%205%2C%20and%2011%20meters%20above%20the%20forest%20floor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETropical%20trees%20absorbed%20the%20most%20methane%2C%20probably%20because%20their%20methane-eating%20microbes%20thrive%20in%20warm%20conditions.%20But%20on%20average%2C%20trees'%20woody%20surface%20makes%20them%20about%2010%25%20more%20climate-beneficial%20than%20previously%20thought%2C%20the%20researchers%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGauci%20noted%20that%20there%20are%20far%20more%20upland%20forests%20than%20wetland%20forests.%20To%20estimate%20the%20full%20scope%20of%20climate%20benefits%2C%20his%20team%20had%20to%20quantify%20the%20surface%20area%20of%20all%20the%20tree%20bark%20in%20the%20world%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20They%20used%20%26quot%3Bterrestrial%20laser%20scanners%26quot%3B%20that%20detect%203D%20tree%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20all%20the%20tree%20bark%20in%20the%20world%20were%20laid%20flat%2C%20it%20would%20cover%20Earth's%20land%20surface%2C%20the%20study%20found.%20And%20it%20may%20be%20removing%20between%2025%20million%20tons%20and%2050%20million%20tons%20of%20methane%20from%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20the%20researchers%20calculated.%20At%20that%20higher%20level%2C%20trees%20could%20be%20removing%20a%20couple%20times%20as%20much%20methane%20than%20what's%20released%20by%20Arctic%20permafrost%20that's%20melting%2C%20Gauci%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20findings%20helped%20close%20a%20discrepancy%20in%20the%20global%20methane%20budget.%20Satellites%20detect%20lower%20methane%20emissions%20than%20what%20scientists%20have%20found%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20implying%20that%20such%20%26quot%3Bbottom-up%26quot%3B%20studies%20either%20overestimated%20methane%20emissions%20or%20missed%20a%20sink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTree%20woody%20surfaces%20add%20a%20third%20dimension%20to%20the%20way%20life%20on%20Earth%20interacts%20with%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20and%20this%20third%20dimension%20is%20teeming%20with%20life%2C%20and%20with%20surprises%2C%26quot%3B%20Yadvinder%20Malhi%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Oxford%20professor%20and%20coauthor%20of%20the%20study%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-groundbreaking-new-reason-to-plant-more-trees-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721913851000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a24ea02d66759f66fe280b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-groundbreaking-new-reason-to-plant-more-trees-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Microbes%20living%20in%20tree%20bark%20are%20absorbing%20methane%2C%20a%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas%2C%20from%20the%20atmosphere%20on%20a%20massive%20scale%2C%20a%20study%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudreau%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Boudreau)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-groundbreaking-new-reason-to-plant-more-trees-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Robots%20might%20solve%20Chipotle's%20portion%20complaints.%20But%20there's%20a%20big%20reason%20they%20won't%20replace%20humans%20%E2%80%94%20yet.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20line%20of%20customers%20stand%20behind%20the%20counter%20of%20a%20makeline%20for%20Chipotle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669c6274fb2b6bedb058f867%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChipotle%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20skimping%20out%20on%20portions.%20A%20robot%20won't%20be%20a%20viable%20solution%2C%20a%20restaurant%20analyst%20told%20BI.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChipotle%20customers%20have%20been%20complaining%20about%20smaller%20portion%20sizes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERobots%20could%20solve%20that%20issue%2C%20but%20they%20would%20take%20away%20from%20a%20key%20Chipotle%20experience%2C%20analyst%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20ability%20to%20ask%20an%20employee%20to%20tweak%20an%20order%20in%20person%20is%20highly%20valuable%2C%20the%20analyst%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fcmg-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChipotle%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20once%20again%20facing%20accusations%20of%20skimping%20out%20on%20portion%20sizes%2C%20and%20while%20robots%20may%20seem%20like%20the%20obvious%20answer%20for%20consistency%2C%20they%20may%20not%20be%20the%20best%20overall%20solution%20for%20the%20restaurant%2C%20an%20analyst%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20customers%20have%20griped%20about%20their%20portion%20sizes%20at%20the%20fast-food%20chain%2C%20and%20Chipotle%20has%20vigorously%20defended%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20no%20changes%20in%20our%20portion%20sizes%2C%20and%20we%20have%20reinforced%20proper%20portioning%20with%20our%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20Laurie%20Schalow%2C%20Chipotle's%20chief%20corporate%20affairs%20and%20food%20safety%20officer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20investors%20appear%20apprehensive%20about%20these%20complaints%2C%20which%20are%20now%20proliferating%20on%20social%20media.%20Some%20activist%20customers%20are%20taking%20matters%20into%20their%20own%20hands%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-customers-film-workers-over-small-portion-sizes-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecording%20employees%20taking%20their%20orders%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20get%20served%20bigger%20scoops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWells%20Fargo%20analysts%20tested%20this%20concern%20by%20ordering%2075%20burrito%20bowls%20and%20weighing%20them.%20The%20team%20found%20that%20the%20portions%20were%20widely%20inconsistent%2C%20with%20the%20heaviest%20bowl%20from%20an%20in-store%20order%20weighing%2047%25%20more%20than%20the%20lightest%20bowl%2C%20the%20analysts%20said%20in%20a%20note%20reported%20by%20Fortune.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20throughput%20is%20improving%2C%20order%20consistency%20remains%20an%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20wrote%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22886b60f6-4ec8-41ca-a64e-7db5ef9ce563%5C%22%3EChipotle's%20stock%20slump%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChipotle's%20shares%20saw%20a%20small%20boost%20on%20Wednesday%20after%20beating%20analysts'%20expectations%20on%20revenue%20and%20earnings%20for%20its%20second%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20overall%2C%20the%20fast-food%20chain's%20stock%20has%20fallen%20from%20its%20record%20peak%20in%20mid-June%20by%2024.5%25%20as%20of%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20company%20underwent%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fbuy-alert-chipotle-stock-set-to-sizzle-after-massive-50-for-1-split-1033535177%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E50-for-1%20stock%20split%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20there%20could%20be%20other%20technical%20reasons%20for%20the%20drop%2C%20Danilo%20Gargiulo%2C%20a%20senior%20analyst%20of%20restaurants%20at%20AllianceBernstein%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20conversations%20around%20portion%20sizes%20likely%20don't%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26