e%20more%20than%20%2414%20billion%20in%20Shuttered%20Venue%20Operators%20Grants.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20firm%2C%20NKSFB%2C%20helped%20its%20clients%2C%20including%20wealthy%20musicians%2C%20tap%20more%20than%20%24200%20million.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECourt%20records%20show%20the%20firm%20worried%20about%20%26quot%3Bperjury%26quot%3B%20and%20negative%20blowback%20before%20going%20ahead.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20Los%20Angeles%20accounting%20firm%20that%20caters%20to%20music%20stars%20was%20privately%20worried%20that%20its%20artists%20could%20be%20breaking%20the%20law%20by%20applying%20for%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20pandemic-era%20grants%20from%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration%2C%20court%20records%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECongress%20created%20the%20Shuttered%20Venue%20Operators%20Grant%20in%202021%20to%20help%20theaters%20and%20indie%20music%20venues%20stay%20in%20business%20during%20the%20pandemic%20lockdowns.%20As%20the%20name%20implies%2C%20the%20grants%20%E2%80%94%20which%20were%20not%20required%20to%20be%20paid%20back%20%E2%80%94%20were%20intended%20for%20theater%20owners%2C%20performing-arts%20companies%2C%20promoters%2C%20producers%2C%20and%20other%20behind-the-scenes%20businesses%20that%20had%20no%20money%20coming%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202023%20Business%20Insider%20investigation%20found%20that%20dozens%20of%20wealthy%20musicians%20used%20ineffective%20oversight%20and%20loopholes%20in%20the%20law%20to%20line%20their%20pockets.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsba-svog-grant-pandemic-relief-fund-post-malone-chris-brown-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPost%20Malone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Chris%20Brown%2C%20Nickelback%2C%20and%20other%20artists%20got%20millions%20in%20taxpayer%20money%20even%20as%20some%20of%20them%20spent%20lavishly%20on%20homes%20and%20other%20acquisitions%20(in%20Post%20Malone's%20case%2C%20he%20spent%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20on%20a%20hobbyist's%20sword-forging%20studio%20shortly%20before%20receiving%20%2410%20million%20in%20grants).%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flil-wayne-post-malone-sba-svog-drug-free-workplace-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELil%20Wayne%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20others%20submitted%20signed%20certifications%20that%20they%20maintained%20drug-free%20workplaces%2C%20a%20requirement%20to%20get%20federal%20grants%2C%20despite%20being%20open%20about%20their%20enthusiasm%20for%20weed%20and%20psychedelic%20drugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SBA%20insisted%20that%20such%20grants%20were%20legal%2C%20an%20argument%20echoed%20by%20industry%20sources.%20But%20newly%20released%20emails%20and%20affidavits%20obtained%20by%20BI%20show%20that%20behind%20the%20scenes%2C%20many%20of%20the%20people%20applying%20for%20SVOG%20funds%20on%20behalf%20of%20wealthy%20artists%20worried%20for%20months%20that%20the%20artists%20didn't%20actually%20qualify.%20And%20at%20least%20one%20artist%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Canadian%20American%20crooner%20Paul%20Anka%20%E2%80%94%20turned%20down%20the%20advice%20of%20a%20consultant%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20grant%20because%20he%20said%20it%20felt%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20newly%20public%20court%20records%2C%20part%20of%20a%20lawsuit%20over%20a%20consultant's%20claims%20that%20he%20is%20entitled%20to%20a%20piece%20of%20the%20grants%2C%20reveal%20how%20word%20of%20the%20program%20traveled.%20Some%20staff%20at%20NKSFB%2C%20an%20accounting%20and%20wealth-management%20firm%20that%20eventually%20helped%20bring%20in%20more%20than%20%24200%20million%20from%20SVOG%20applications%2C%20were%20initially%20hesitant%20to%20submit%20applications%20for%20their%20clients'%20touring%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Hickok%2C%20a%20business%20manager%2C%20wrote%20in%20an%20affidavit%20that%20despite%20murmurs%20within%20the%20industry%20that%20artists%20were%20cashing%20in%2C%20within%20his%20division%20of%20the%20firm%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20came%20to%20a%20consensus%20that%20applying%20for%20SVOG%20grants%20on%20behalf%20of%20musicians'%20touring%20entities%20was%20too%20risky.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20SVOG%20guidelines%20did%20not%20specifically%20mention%20touring%20entities%20as%20an%20eligible%20category%2C%20and%20our%20primary%20concern%20was%20that%20the%20client%20might%20receive%20the%20award%20and%20then%20later%20have%20to%20return%20it%20after%20an%20audit%20initiated%20by%20the%20SBA%2C%26quot%3B%20Hickok%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20people%20at%20NKSFB%20were%20worried%20that%20their%20clients%20would%20face%20bad%20publicity%20if%20they%20sought%20a%20grant%20or%20that%20the%20government%20could%20try%20to%20claw%20the%20money%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20information%20about%20awarded%20grants%20was%20public%2C%20so%20not%20only%20would%20this%20put%20a%20financial%20burden%20on%20the%20client%2C%20but%20it%20could%20also%20harm%20the%20client's%20reputation%2C%26quot%3B%20Hickok%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIf%20NKSFB%2C%20as%20a%20fiduciary%2C%20advised%20its%20clients%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20grant%20for%20which%20they%20would%20ultimately%20be%20found%20ineligible%2C%20that%20would%20result%20in%20negative%20consequences%20for%20our%20clients%2C%20and%20could%20also%20expose%20NKSFB%20to%20liability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20June%202021%20email%2C%20Bessy%20Wong%2C%20an%20NKSFB%20partner%2C%20told%20the%20firm's%20managing%20partner%2C%20Mickey%20Segal%2C%20that%20she%20told%20Anka%20that%20Segal%20was%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20%26quot%3Bhe%20could%20be%20committing%20perjury%20by%20filing%20for%20the%20government%20grant%20when%20he%20wasn't%20entitled%20to%20the%20funds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20NKSFB%20was%20under%20pressure%20from%20clients%20who%20claimed%20the%20practice%20was%20widespread.%20%26quot%3BAll%20the%20top%20acts%20are%20doing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20talent%20manager%20for%20Suicideboys%2C%20Kyle%20Leunissen%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20July%2027%2C%202021%2C%20email.%20Federal%20records%20show%20that%20the%20hip-hop%20duo's%20touring%20company%20got%20%243.6%20million%20in%20August%20that%20year.%20In%20October%2C%20Billboard%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.billboard.com%2Fmusic%2Fmusic-news%2Fsuicideboys-new-album-headlining-tour-2021-interview-9649488%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Suicideboys%20signed%20a%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20eight-figure%20deal%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20distributor.%20Leunissen%20didn't%20reply%20to%20an%20email%20seeking%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccountants%20at%20the%20firm%20were%20also%20made%20aware%20of%20industry%20efforts%20to%20pressure%20the%20SBA%2C%20including%20through%20Congress%2C%20to%20interpret%20the%20law%20broadly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLaw%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20be%20interpreted%20on%20intent%20but%20on%20language%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Strickland%2C%20a%20lawyer%20who%20owns%20the%20concert-lighting%20business%20Bandit%20Lites%2C%20said%20in%20an%20April%202021%20email%20sent%20to%20others%20in%20the%20industry.%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20emails%20you%20send%2C%20the%20harder%20it%20is%20for%20the%20SBA%20to%20exclude%20sectors%20based%20on%20'intent.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrickland%20told%20BI%20he%20pushed%20for%20focusing%20aid%20on%20those%20most%20in%20need.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20into%20a%20long-term%2C%20very%20lengthy%2C%20very%20in-depth%20conversation%20with%20all%20of%20the%20people%20behind%20Save%20Our%20Stages%2C%20saying%20we%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20this%20goes%20to%20the%20most%20needy%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20once%20the%20law%20was%20passed%2C%20Strickland%20said%20he%20focused%20on%20helping%20as%20many%20people%20get%20money%20as%20possible.%20He%20was%20frank%20about%20the%20program's%20shortcomings%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20met%20the%20letter%20of%20the%20law%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20was%20written%20wide%20open%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20a%20bunch%20of%20folks%20that%20bought%20jet%20cards.%20There%20was%20nothing%20in%20there%20that%20said%20you%20had%20to%20pay%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrickland%20added%20that%20the%20problem%20went%20beyond%20wealthy%20recipients%3A%20%26quot%3BForget%20the%20people%20who%20have%20money%3A%20There%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20abuse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Hickok's%20affidavit%2C%20the%20turning%20point%20for%20NKSFB%20came%20in%20late%20August%202021%2C%20just%20two%20days%20before%20the%20deadline%20to%20file%20an%20SVOG%20application.%20At%20a%20meeting%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20they%20concluded%20the%20larger%20risk%20was%20being%20fired%20or%20perhaps%20even%20sued%20if%20they%20didn't%20give%20their%20clients%20the%20grants%20versus%20whatever%20the%20risks%20were%20of%20applying%20for%20them.%20The%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20clients%20chose%20to%20apply%2C%20Hickok%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20who%20didn't%3A%20Paul%20Anka.%20According%20to%20an%20email%2C%20he%20ended%20up%20telling%20NKSFB%20to%20pull%20the%20application%2C%20figuring%20he%20was%20being%20fed%20%26quot%3BBS%26quot%3B%20by%20a%20consultant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnksfb-svog-blowback-rich-musicians-pandemic-relief-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721912206000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669ece2880d4d5da13d612ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnksfb-svog-blowback-rich-musicians-pandemic-relief-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Top%20accountants%20for%20superstar%20musicians%20at%20NKSFB%20worried%20their%20clients%20could%20not%20legally%20claim%20COVID%20cash.%20Then%20they%20changed%20their%20minds.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jnewsham%40insider.com%20(Jack%20Newsham)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnksfb-svog-blowback-rich-musicians-pandemic-relief-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Southwest%20is%20ditching%20its%20unassigned%20seat%20policy%20for%20the%20first%20time%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226244%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Southwest%20Airlines%20planes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669c152c80d4d5da13d5a0c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223958%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESouthwest%20Airlines%20said%20Thursday%20that%20it%20will%20join%20almost%20every%20other%20major%20airline%20in%20assigning%20seats%20prior%20to%20boarding.%20%3Cp%3EKevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthwest-airlines-history-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESouthwest%20Airlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20had%20an%20unassigned%20seating%20policy%20for%20over%2050%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20carrier%20now%20plans%20to%20assign%20seats%20on%20all%20flights%20and%20offer%20premium%20seating%20options.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20changes%20come%20as%20the%20airline%20faces%20pressure%20from%20activist%20investor%20Elliott%20Investment%20Management.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESouthwest%20Airlines%20is%20eliminating%20its%20open%20seating%20model%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20Instead%2C%20it%20will%20start%20assigning%20seats%20before%20all%20flights%20and%20offering%20premium%20seating%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fswamedia.com%2Freleases%2Frelease-66ab759a702a76e0bcb37c45465c6a58-southwest-airlines-launches-enhancements-to-transform-customer-experience-and-improve-financial-performance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannouncement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday%20is%20part%20of%20the%20airline's%20mission%20to%20improve%20financial%20performance%2C%20increase%20its%20stock%20price%2C%20and%20enhance%20customer%20experience.%20It%20comes%20as%20