20and%20direction%20%E2%80%94%20could%20have%20pushed%20the%20plane%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Katz%2C%20a%20veteran%20commercial%20pilot%2C%20told%20The%20Tampa%20Bay%20Times%20that%20wind%20shear%20could%20have%20%26quot%3Bswatted%20the%20airplane%20like%20a%20fly%20into%20Tampa%20Bay.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20so%2C%20Katz%20said%20it%20doesn't%20explain%20why%20the%20pilots%20didn't%20seem%20to%20be%20aware%20that%20they%20were%20flying%20at%20a%20dangerous%20height.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20pilots%20are%20going%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20explaining%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Katz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2211430b76-1044-4481-a909-c9e99b20646a%5C%22%3EA%20dangerous%20pattern%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20first%20time%20a%20Southwest%20flight%20has%20descended%20to%20a%20dangerously%20low%20altitude.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%20the%20FAA%20said%20it%20was%20investigating%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthwest-flight-drops-525-feet-above-town-prompting-faa-probe-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESouthwest%20flight%20that%20dropped%20to%20525%20feet%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20was%209%20miles%20from%20landing%20in%20Oklahoma%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20is%20also%20looking%20into%20another%20Southwest%20flight%20that%20descended%20to%20400%20feet%20above%20the%20ocean%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Kauai%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%2C%20a%20Southwest%20spokesperson%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bfollowing%20its%20robust%20safety%20management%20system%26quot%3B%20and%20was%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20FAA%20to%20%26quot%3Bunderstand%20and%20address%20any%20irregularities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNothing%20is%20more%20important%20to%20Southwest%20than%20the%20safety%20of%20our%20customers%20and%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthwest-flight-tampa-low-descent-human-error-experts-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721910353000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a237372d66759f66fe2120%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthwest-flight-tampa-low-descent-human-error-experts-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Southwest%20flight%20is%20being%20investigated%20after%20it%20flew%20dangerously%20close%20to%20Tampa's%20Courtney%20Campbell%20Causeway.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mfriel%40businessinsider.com%20(Mikhaila%20Friel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthwest-flight-tampa-low-descent-human-error-experts-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sunita%20Williams%20'Gardening'%20In%20Space%20As%2010-Day%20Test%20Flight%20Goes%20Beyond%2050%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EHaving%20taken%20off%20on%20Boeing%20Starliner's%20maiden%20flight%20for%20what%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%2010-day%20mission%2C%20Indian-origin%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%20has%20now%20been%20in%20space%20for%2050%20days%20and%20counting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Starliner%20has%20faced%20glitches%20in%20the%20propulsion%20system%20following%20a%20series%20of%20helium%20leaks%20but%20NASA%20has%20said%20Ms%20Williams%20and%20her%20fellow%20astronaut%2C%20Barry%20%26quot%3BButch%26quot%3B%20Wilmore%20are%20safely%20aboard%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%2C%20where%20they%20have%20been%20assisting%20the%20Expedition%2071%20crew%20of%20seven%20astronauts%20with%20maintenance%20as%20well%20as%20various%20experiments%20since%20June%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20space%20agency%20said%20Ms%20Williams%2C%20who%20is%20a%20veteran%20and%20is%20on%20her%20third%20space%20mission%2C%20investigated%20using%20fluid%20physics%2C%20such%20as%20surface%20tension%2C%20to%20overcome%20the%20lack%20of%20gravity%20when%20watering%20and%20nourishing%20plants%20being%20grown%20in%20space.%20This%20is%20akin%20to%20gardening%20in%20space%20and%20is%20a%20very%20vital%20step%20towards%20understanding%20how%20plants%20grow%20and%20respond%20to%20microgravity%20conditions.%20The%20research%20will%20be%20crucial%20when%20humanity%20looks%20to%20establish%20various%20bases%20in%20the%20solar%20system%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Williams%20and%20Mr%20Wilmore%20also%20participated%20in%20vein%20scans%20using%20an%20ultrasound%20device.%20Doctors%20on%20the%20ground%20monitored%20in%20real-time%20as%20the%20pair%20took%20turns%20imaging%20veins%20in%20each%20other's%20neck%2C%20shoulder%2C%20and%20legs.%20Ms%20Wilmore%20also%20scanned%20the%20veins%20of%20fellow%20NASA%20astronaut%20Matthew%20Dominick%2C%20helping%20researchers%20understand%20how%20microgravity%20affects%20the%20human%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvanced%20biology%20research%20is%20also%20underway%20aboard%20the%20orbiting%20lab%20with%20astronauts%20exploring%20how%20living%20in%20space%20affects%20the%20human%20body%20and%20mind.%20Ms%20Williams%20extracted%20DNA%20to%20identify%20microbe%20samples%20collected%20from%20water%20systems%20aboard%20the%20ISS%2C%20which%20is%20like%20a%20mini-city%20in%20space%20and%20has%20been%20flying%20for%2025%20years.%20Results%20from%20the%20genetic%20biotechnology%20experiment%20may%20improve%20ways%20to%20keep%20crews%20healthy%20and%20spacecraft%20systems%20clean%20on%20future%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReturn%20Date%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20on%20terra%20firma%2C%20Boeing%20engineers%20have%20been%20testing%20replicas%20of%20thrusters%20on%20Earth%20to%20try%20and%20figure%20out%20what%20went%20wrong%20with%20the%20Starliner%20and%20how%20to%20safely%20bring%20back%20the%20spacecraft%20and%20its%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20update%2C%20NASA%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BEngineering%20teams%20with%20NASA%20and%20Boeing%20recently%20completed%20ground%20hot%20fire%20testing%20of%20a%20Starliner%20reaction%20control%20system%20thruster%20at%20White%20Sands%20Test%20Facility%20in%20New%20Mexico%2C%20USA.%20The%20test%20series%20involved%20firing%20the%20engine%20through%20similar%20in-flight%20conditions%20the%20spacecraft%20experienced%20during%20its%20approach%20to%20the%20space%20station%2C%20as%20well%20as%20various%20stress-case%20firings%20for%20what%20is%20expected%20during%20Starliner's%20undocking%20and%20the%20deorbit%20burn%20that%20will%20position%20the%20spacecraft%20for%20a%20landing%20in%20the%20southwestern%20United%20States.%20Teams%20are%20analysing%20the%20data%20from%20these%20tests.'%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20engineers%20are%20expected%20to%20give%20an%20update%20on%20these%20tests%20on%20Thursday%20and%20may%20also%20announce%20the%20likely%20date%20of%20Ms%20Williams%20and%20Mr%20Wilmore's%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721910060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fbl93e5h_sunita-williams-from-space_625x300_10_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsunita-williams-gardening-in-space-as-10-day-test-flight-stretches-beyond-50-6186523%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Having%20taken%20off%20on%20Boeing%20Starliner's%20maiden%20flight%20for%20what%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%2010-day%20mission%2C%20Indian-origin%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%20has%20now%20been%20in%20space%20for%2050%20days%20and%20counting.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsunita-williams-gardening-in-space-as-10-day-test-flight-stretches-beyond-50-6186523%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsunita-williams-gardening-in-space-as-10-day-test-flight-stretches-beyond-50-6186523%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22amp