org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fashok-leyland-q1-fy25-results-net-profit-declines-6-to-rs-509-crore-124072501034_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fashok-leyland-q1-fy25-results-net-profit-declines-6-to-rs-509-crore-124072501034_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MiG-27%20Ejection%2C%20Then%20Gun%20In%20Mouth%3A%20Kargil%20War%20Hero%20Recounts%20Capture%20In%20Pak%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Kargil%20War%2025%20years%20back%2C%20K%20Nachiketa%20Rao%2C%20then%20a%20flight%20lieutenant%20with%20Indian%20Air%20Force%2C%20survived%20a%20tryst%20with%20death.%20Forced%20to%20eject%20from%20a%20MiG-27%20fighter%20jet%20after%20its%20engine%20failed%2C%20he%20was%20captured%20as%20a%20Prisoner%20of%20War%20by%20Pakistan%20troops.%20He%20survived%20for%20eight%20days%20there%20before%20he%20was%20handed%20over%20to%20Indian%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20NDTV%20revisits%20the%20Kargil%20War%20and%20remembers%20sacrifices%20and%20acts%20of%20bravery%20by%20Indian%20soldiers%2C%20we%20spoke%20to%20the%20brave%20fighter%20pilot%2C%20who%20retired%20from%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20as%20a%20Group%20Captain%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Ejection%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecounting%20the%20events%20on%20the%20day%20that%20would%20change%20his%20life%20forever%2C%20Group%20Captain%20Nachiketa%20Rao%20(retd)%20said%20he%20had%20taken%20off%20with%20three%20other%20fighter%20pilots%20from%20Srinagar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20became%20airborne%20from%20Srinagar...%20and%20the%20target%20was%20at%20a%20place%20called%20Munthu%20Dhalo.%20There%20was%20a%20huge%20enemy%20logistics%20hub%20there.%20We%20got%20airborne%20in%20a%20set%20of%20four%20aeroplanes.%20Me%20and%20my%20leader%2C%20we%20were%20firing%20rockets.%20After%20the%20rocket%20attack%2C%20I%20had%20an%20engine%20failure.%20A%20MiG%2027%20is%20a%20single%20engine%20aeroplane%2C%20and%20in%20case%20of%20an%20engine%20failure%2C%20I%20followed%20the%20relight%20process%2C%20but%20since%20the%20(ground)%20altitude%20was%20very%20high%2C%20I%20ran%20out%20of%20height.%20Once%20I%20saw%20the%20hills%20gushing%20towards%20my%20aeroplane%2C%20I%20had%20no%20option%20but%20to%20eject%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20at%20the%20time%2C%20he%20was%20flying%20at%20an%20altitude%20of%20more%20than%2015%2C000%20feet.%C2%A0%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20fortunate%20decision%20because%20within%20a%20few%20seconds%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20got%20my%20senses%20back%2C%20I%20could%20see%20the%20airplane%20crashing%20onto%20the%20hillside.%20I%20could%20have%20gone%20with%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Capture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20young%20fighter%20pilot's%20problems%20were%20far%20from%20over.%20%26quot%3BThe%20comfort%20of%20a%20fighter%20jet%20cockpit%20had%20gone%20away.%20For%20a%20fighter%20pilot%2C%20it's%20very%20important.%20There%20was%20snow%20all%20around%2C%20my%20body%20was%20not%20acclimatised%2C%20and%20just%20one%20small%20pistol%20and%2016%20rounds%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlight%20Lieutenant%20Nachiketa%20did%20not%20know%20where%20he%20was.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20hiding%20classified%20information%20with%20me%20and%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20sense%20of%20the%20situation.%20I%20could%20hear%20a%20lot%20of%20firing.%20I%20could%20not%20figure%20out%20if%20it%20was%20aimed%20at%20me.%20So%20I%20ran%20to%20take%20cover%20behind%20some%20boulders.%20I%20then%20saw%20five-six%20troopers.%20By%20then%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20I%20was%20not%20in%20an%20area%20where%20our%20forces%20were%20camping.%20I%20fired%20my%20pistol%2C%20but%20eight%20rounds%20finished%20very%20fast.%20Before%20I%20could%20load%20the%20other%20magazine%2C%20one%20of%20them%20had%20reached%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTwenty%20five%20years%20is%20a%20very%20long%20time%2C%20but%20even%20now%2C%20that%20guy's%20eyes%20and%20face%20are%20clear%20in%20my%20mind.%20He%20shoved%20the%20barrel%20of%20his%20AK%2047%20in%20my%20mouth%20and%20I%20was%20looking%20at%20his%20trigger%20finger%2C%20whether%20he%20will%20pull%20it%20or%20not.%20But%20destiny%20has%20its%20designs.%20The%20Army%20captain%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20platoon%20stopped%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20retired%20Air%20Force%20officer%2C%20who%20now%20flies%20commercial%20flights.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20Pakistani%20Army%20captain%20was%20able%20to%20convince%20his%20colleagues%20that%20the%20Indian%20pilot%20was%20just%20doing%20his%20duty%20as%20a%20soldier.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20made%20a%20captive%20and%20we%20went%20to%20the%20campsite%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20POW%20Nightmare%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGroup%20Captain%20Nachiketa%20Rao%20(retd)%C2%A0%C2%A0said%20he%20did%20not%20know%20his%20location%20at%20that%20point.%20But%2C%20some%20years%20back%2C%20when%20he%20returned%20to%20the%20same%20area%20in%20an%20Army%20helicopter%2C%20he%20realised%20that%20the%20camp%20was%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%2C%20about%206%20kilometres%20from%20the%20Line%20of%20Control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20ejection%20had%20left%20him%20with%20some%20back%20pain%20and%20cold%20was%20seeping%20into%20his%20shoes.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20respect%20for%20that%20Captain%20at%20a%20person-to-person%20level.%20He%20saved%20me%20from%20his%20troopers%20and%20when%20they%20captured%20me%20and%20here%2C%20he%20gave%20me%20first-aid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20our%20Army%20finally%20took%20over%20this%20area%20and%20the%20entire%20part%20of%20land%20came%20back%20to%20us%2C%20this%20(Pakistani)%20Army%20officer%20was%20killed.%20I%20got%20to%20know%20because%20I%20got%20an%20extract%20of%20his%20diary%20from%20our%20Army%20intelligence%20sources.%20I%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20respect%20for%20him%20for%20the%20way%20he%20treated%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20officer%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20camp%2C%20the%20captive%20Indian%20pilot%20was%20then%20put%20into%20a%20helicopter%20and%20taken%20to%20Skardu.%20There%20he%20underwent%20what%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20interrogation%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20about%2024%20hours%2C%20a%20C130%20(aircraft)%20came%20and%20I%20was%20shifted%20to%20Islamabad%20and%20then%20Rawalpindi.%20They%20took%20about%20one%20day%20to%20declare%20me%20uncooperative.%20That%20is%20when%20they%20handed%20me%20over%20to%20the%20ISI%20specialist%20cell%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20airman%20described%20what%20came%20next%20as%20%26quot%3Bquite%20bad%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BStaying%20alone%20in%20the%20cell%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20integration%20techniques%20of%2C%20heat%2C%20standing%2C%20hitting%2C%20no%20food.%20It%20becomes%20very%20tough%20because%20they%20want%20to%20break%20you%20mentally%2C%20physically%2C%20emotionally%20so%20that%20you%20start%20talking.%20But%2C%20I%20was%20again%20a%20bit%20lucky%20because%20by%20the%20time%20this%20part%20gets%20over%2C%20we%20get%20into%20a%20state%2C%20called%20drugs%20or%20third%20degree.%20In%20case%20they%20start%20third%20degree%2C%20I%20got%20to%20know%20later%2C%20the%20situation%20of%20being%20sent%20back%20is%20not%20there.%20Up%20till%20now%2C%20all%20the%20injuries%20they%20can%20explain%20by%20saying%20that%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20escape%20and%20all%20these%20things%20happened.%20But%20when%20third%20degree%20starts%2C%20you'll%20have%20marks%20on%20the%20body%20they%20can't%20explain.%20I%20was%20lucky%20that%20before%20that%20stage%20came%2C%20the%20decision%20to%20get%20me%20back%20to%20India%20had%20come.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDescribing%20the%20torture%20he%20went%20through%2C%20Group%20Captain%20Nachiketa%20(retd)%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20systematic%20process.%20So%20they%20step%20up%20the%20process%20and%20see%20where%20you'll%20break.%20Physical%20hardship%2C%20then%20mental%20hardship%2C%20then%20heat%20treatment.%20High%20voltage%20bulbs%20on%20the%20cell%20pointing%20towards%20you.%20Denial%20of%20food%2C%20denial%20of%20sleep.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20pain%20of%20not%20eating%2C%20pain%20of%20not%20sleeping%2C%20the%20physical%20pain%20of%20being%20hit%20on%20the%20body%2C%20or%20the%20mental%20pain.%20Now%20you%20start%20thinking%20which%20pain%20is%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20it%20has%20taken%20him%20so%20many%20years%20to%20be%20able%20to%20talk%20about%20this%2C%20the%20retired%20fighter%20pilot%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20retired%20in%202017.%20So%20till%20the%20time%20of%20serving%2C%20we%20don't%20talk%20of%20all%20this.%20So%20I%20did%20not%20speak.%20And%20after%20retirement%2C%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%2C%20actually%2C%20when%20I'm%20coming%20out%20to%20a%20place%20like%20this%20where%20I%20am%20interacting%20with%20media%20personnel%20like%20you.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20part%20POW%20phase%20is%20not%20a%20very%20comfortable%20(subject)%20to%20talk%20about.%20Sometimes%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20some%20hidden%20trauma%20that%20can%20come%20back.%20So%20usually%2C%20I%20avoid%20talking%20about%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Good%20News%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDescribing%20the%20moment%20of%20relief%20when%20he%20found%20that%20he%20was%20coming%20home%2C%20the%20retired%20officer%20said%20that%20he%20was%20sent%20to%20a%20safe%20house%20and%20given%20new%20clothes.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20people%20gave%20me%20food%2C%20and%20I%20got%20all%20the%20basic%20facilities%20back.%20I%20could%20make%20out%20that%20something%20had%20changed.%20They%20did%20not%20tell%20me%20at%20that%20stage%2C%20but%20I%20could%20sense%20something%20had%20changed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20after%20some%20rest%2C%20he%20was%20taken%20to%20International%20Red%20Cross%20Society.%20Prisoners%20of%20war%2C%20he%20said%2C%20are%20not%20handed%20over%20directly%20to%20the%20other%20nations%20just%20to%20preclude%20future%20implications.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they%20have%20basic%20medical%20check-ups%20are%20there.%20After%20some%20documentation%2C%20they%20handed%20me%20over%20to%20the%20Indian%20embassy.%20I%20spoke%20to%20my%20parents%2C%20told%20them%20I%20am%20fine.%20Then%20I%20had%20a%20word%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfter%20The%20Return%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20miraculous%20return%2C%20Group%20Captain%20Nachiketa%20(retd)%20did%20not%20fly%20fighter%20jets%2C%20but%20was%20moved%20to%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20it%20was%20due%20to%20an%20injury%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20happens%20is%20when%20you%2C%20eject%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20tall%2C%20you%20can%20have%2C%20something%20called%20compression%20injuries%20on%20the%20spinal%20cord.%20In%20my%20case%2C%20that%20was%20complicated%20by%20no%20rest%20after%20the%20ejection.%20I%20had%20a%20multiple%20compression%20on%20the%20dorsal%20part%20of%20the%20spine.%20So%20the%20medical%20procedure%20which%20took%20about%203%20to%204%20years%20indicated%20that%20I%20cannot%20fly%20the%20ejection%20seat%20once%20again.%20So%20I%20was%20shifted%20to%20transport%20airplanes.%20During%20these%203%20to%204%20years%2C%20I%20flew%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicles.%20I%20flew%20transport%20planes%2C%20then%20I%20retired%20in%202017%20and%20moved%20to%20commercial%20flights.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20heart%20of%20a%20pilot%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20in%20the%20cockpit%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BWhichever%20aeroplane%20you%20fly%2C%20as%20long%20as%20you're%20flying%2C%20that's%20so%20beautiful%20and%20divine%2C%20other%20things%20don't%20matter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20hero%20wears%20his%20bravery%20lightly%20on%20his%20shoulders.%20%26quot%3BAll%20of%20us%2C%20all%20soldiers%20and%20martyrs%2C%201%2C000%20plus%20people%20who%20got%20injured%2C%20have%20done%20the%20same%20job%2C%20a%20focused%20effort%20to%20get%20an%20area%20back%20that%20was%20taken%20by%20the%20infiltrators.%20It%20is%20just%20that%20I%20was%20on%20MiG%2027%2C%20which%20has%20more%20visibility%2C%20more%20glamour%2C%20and%20higher%20speeds.%20Otherwise%2C%20I'm%20sure%20all%20of%20us%20are%20basically%20soldiers%20at%20heart%20doing%20a%20job%20which%20for%20which%20we%20signed%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20with%20a%20smile.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721909580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2F3gvupg3_group-captain-nachiketa_625x300_25_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fk-nachiketa-rao-kargil-war-mig-27-ejection-then-gun-in-mouth-kargil-war-hero-recounts-capture-in-pak-6186518%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22During%20the%20Kargil%20War%2025%20years%20back%2C%20K%20Nachiketa%20Rao%2C%20then%20a%20flight%20lieutenant%20with%20Indian%20Air%20Force%2C%20survived%20a%20tryst%20with%20death.%20Forced%20to%20eject%20from%20a%20MiG-27%20fighter%20jet%20after%20its%20engine%20failed%2C%20he%20found%20himself%20in%20Pakistani%20territory%20and%20was%20capt%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fk-nachiketa-rao-kargil-war-mig-27-ejection-then-gun-in-mouth-kargil-war-hero-recounts-capture-in-pak-6186518%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fk-nachiketa-rao-kargil-war-mig-27-ejection-then-gun-in-mouth-kargil-war-hero-recounts-capture-in-pak-6186518%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fk-nachiketa-rao-kargil-war-mig-27-ejection-then-gun-in-mouth-kargil-war-hero-recounts-capture-in