.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGymkhana%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpulence%20and%20grandeur%20are%20the%20theme%20of%20the%20day%20at%20Gymkhana%20in%20London%2C%20which%20evokes%20the%20same%20mystique%20that%20colonial%20Indian%20clubs%20frequented%20by%20the%20elite%2C%20did.%20The%20restaurant%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20awarded%20two%20MICHELIN%20Stars%20in%202024%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20product%20of%20the%20Sethi%20siblings%20%E2%80%94%20Jyotin%2C%20Karam%20and%20Sunaina%20%E2%80%94%20who%20are%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20the%20restaurant%20empire%20in%20the%20UK%20with%20Trishna%2C%20Gymkhana%2C%20and%20Hoppers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20its%20brilliant%20range%20of%20foods%2C%20Gymkhana%20also%20retails%20its%20famous%20butter%20%3Cem%3Emasala%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20Goan%20curry%20%3Cem%3Emasala%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20flavours%20of%20cumin%2C%20coriander%20and%20turmeric%3B%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F156155%2Fharappa-to-japan-the-story-of-curry-how-it-got-its-name%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evindaloo%20masala%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20spicy%20Indian%20%3Cem%3Emasala%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewith%20a%20hot%20and%20sour%20taste)%3B%20and%20%3Cem%3Erogan%20josh%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20slow-cooked%20classic%20made%20using%20the%20finest%20chillies%20from%20Kashmir).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E9.%20Junoon%2C%20New%20York%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fmichelin-star-indian-restaurants-4-1721655289.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Junoon%20in%20New%20York%20has%20a%20menu%20that%20is%20focused%20on%20bold%20flavours%2C%20Indian%20chaats%20and%20mutton%20curries%2C%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D